The paper deals with inverse problems in image processing and proposes a method to use deep neural networks to speed up convergence rates of conventional optimization-based methods. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves optimization algorithms, indicating that it could also belong to the information theory (cs.IT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses deep neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
